      "comment": "UNIQUELY IDEAL (8) was out of the money two runs back at Ballarat then improved sharply last start to score by a head over 1690m at Kilmore. Won't spend a penny from this draw but luck may play a role on the bell lap. It doesn't get any easier but she is capable of making it consecutive wins. KOMODO (4) finished third at Ballarat two runs ago before finishing seventh at his latest appearance over 2240m at Melton, beaten 7 metres. Meets a comparable field and he can give this a mighty shake. LEWIELEWIS (1) is worth plenty of thought off a last-start win by 2 metres at Boort over 2250m. MADIGAN (10) must be considered after he finished runner-up over 2195m at Ararat nine days ago.",
